Chinese court jails respected Uighur academic for life | The Times

A respected university academic who dared to speak out for the rights of 
China’s Uighur ethnic minority has been found guilty of inciting separatism 
and jailed for life.


Close friends of Ilham Tohti, who taught economics at Minzu University in 
Beijing until his arrest in January, told The Times that his trial 
was part of a dangerous spiral of state repression and censorship that would 
inevitably lead to greater violence in the restive region of Xinjiang.


As police across Xinjiang reinforced an already massive security operation, 
Beijing moved to squash any online discussion of the academic’s downfall and 
barred Professor

